title: College soccer: Armstrong’s goal powers SUNY Canton in overtime
text:
A A 
CANTON — Aliza Armstrong scored off a pass from Katie Lamica in the 98th minute to give the SUNY Canton women’s soccer team a 2-1 overtime victory over SUNY Polytechnic in a nonconference game Thursday night. 
Lamica also assisted on a goal by Brittany Pierce in the 40th minute for the Kangaroos (3-4-2 overall). SUNY Poly (5-2-2) sent the game to overtime when Brittany Waterbury scored in the 77th minute on a free kick from just outside the box. 
■ Thomas Leech supplied a goal and two assists as the host Jefferson CC men’s soccer team beat Finger Lakes CC, 3-1, in Mid-State Athletic Conference game. 
Eric Gibbs and Scott Dalby added goals for the Cannoneers (4-4, 2-2). Quinton Ashley scored for the Lakers (1-10, 1-2). 
■ Abigail Keenan registered three goals to lift Finger Lakes Community College to a 5-2 victory over Jefferson CC in a Mid-State Athletic Conference women’s soccer game in Canandaigua. 
Kerstin Phelps scored twice for the Cannoneers (1-3-1 overall, 0-2-1 league). Commenting rules: Stick to the topic of the article/letter/editorial. When responding to issues raised by other commenters, do not engage in personal attacks or name-calling.
